flowRoot.flowPara: The regions in this map have been color-coded with the ternary balance scheme as displayed in Figure a. Bright and vivid colors indicate regions where most people have the same education level, whereas desaturated and dark colors indicate a more diverse population composition.

A ternary diagram showing the population composition by education level for each European NUTS-2 region in 2016, ages 25–64. The colors correspond to the ternary balance scheme used to color Map b and show direction (via hue) and magnitude (via lightness and saturation) of the deviation from a perfectly balanced composition.
